Competition: Copa America
Season: 1935
Country: Peru
BlockSource: http://www.rsssf.com/tables/35safull.html

* Peru, January 6-27. All games played in Lima. The champion qualifies to Berlin Olympic Games. However, as Uruguay and Argentina had to renounce to the qualification due to economic problems Peru was chosen to represent South America. Brazil, Bolivia and Paraguay withdrew.

06.01.35  Lima, Stadium Nacional
ARG - CHI 4:1 (1:1)
(25,000) Miguel Serra Hurtado PER
ARG: Bello - Wilson, Scarcella - De Jonge, Minella, De Mare (45 Pajoni) - Lauri, Sastre,Masantonio, Zito (46 García), Arrieta
CHI: R.Cortés - Welch, A.Cortés - Gornall, Riveros, Araneda - Aranda, Giudice, Carmona(46 Sorrel), Vidal, Avilés
0:1 Carmona 8, 1:1 Lauri 28, 2:1 Arrieta 49, 3:1 García 57, 4:1 Masantonio 71

